1956年，鲍尔斯以[[上尉|上尉]][[军衔|军衔]]从空军退役。随后，他加入了美国中央情报局的U-2计划。U-2计划飞行员利用可以升到七万英尺（约合21.3千米）高空的U-2飞机进行[[间谍|间谍]]任务。U-2装备了当时最先进的专门设计为从包括[[苏联|苏联]]在内的敌对国家上空[[平流层|平流层]]的边缘拍摄高分辨率照片的照相机。U-2的任务在于系统的拍摄军事设施和其他重要的地点。<!--Powers was discharged from the Air Force in 1956 with the rank of [[Captain_(U.S._Air_Force)|captain]]. He then joined the CIA's [[Lockheed_U-2|U-2]] program at the civilian grade of GS-12. U-2 pilots flew [[espionage|espionage]] missions using an aircraft that could reach altitudes above 70,000 feet (21,3km), making it invulnerable to Soviet anti-aircraft weapons of the time. The U-2 was equipped with a state-of-the-art camera designed to take high-resolution photos from the edge of the stratosphere over hostile countries, including the [[Soviet_Union|Soviet Union]]. U-2 missions systematically photographed military installations and other important sites.-->

自1956年起，苏联情报机关尤其是[[克格勃|克格勃]]就已经开始注意到U-2的活动，但直到1960年他们对此都缺乏有效的应对措施。1960年5月1日，鲍尔斯驾驶的U-2在执行由[[巴基斯坦|巴基斯坦]][[白沙瓦|白沙瓦]]附近的一处军用机场起飞<ref name = "unattn"/>，并且可能由美军在{{le|伯德埃波|Badaber}}的空军基站（{{link-en|白沙瓦空军基地|Peshawar Air Station}}）提供支援执行侦察任务时，在[[斯维尔德洛夫斯克|斯维尔德洛夫斯克]]上空被[[S-75导弹|S-75德维纳]]（SA-2地对空）导弹击落<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.astronautix.com/lvs/s75.htm |title=S-75 |publisher=Astronautix.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-31 |language=en |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121005194237/http://astronautix.com/lvs/s75.htm |archivedate=2012-10-05 }}</ref>。在鲍尔斯跳伞降落到地面并被捕获前并未启动飞机的自毁装置。
<!--Soviet intelligence, especially the [[KGB|KGB]], had been aware of U-2 missions since 1956, but they lacked effective counter-measures until 1960. Powers’ U-2, which departed from a military airbase in [[Peshawar|Peshawar]], [[Pakistan|Pakistan]]<ref name = "unattn"/> and may have received support from the US Air Station at Badaber ([[Peshawar_Air_Station|Peshawar Air Station]]), was shot down by an [[S-75_Dvina|S-75 Dvina]] (SA-2 Surface to Air) missile on May 1, 1960, over [[Yekaterinburg|Sverdlovsk]]. Powers was unable to activate the plane's self-destruct mechanism before he parachuted to the ground and was captured.-->

现有资料表示当时总计发射有8枚导弹，鲍尔斯的U-2被第一枚击中并起火<ref>"Таким образом, всего по Lockheed U-2 и двум МиГ было выпущено семь ракет. Еще одну (восьмую) ракету выпустил зенитный ракетный дивизион соседнего полка под командованием полковника Ф. Савинова." {{cite web|url=http://vpk-news.ru/articles/6393|title=Юрий Кнутов, Олег Фаличев. Бой в небе над Уралом|publisher=Военно-промышленный курьер|accessdate=2013-11-09|language=ru|archive-date=2014-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140106103208/http://vpk-news.ru/articles/6393|dead-url=no}}</ref>。一枚导弹击中了苏联方面派出进行U-2拦截行动的[[米格-19战斗机|米格-19战斗机]]。由于高度不足，苏联飞行员谢尔盖·萨夫罗诺夫为避免坠机发生在[[杰格佳尔斯克|杰格佳尔斯克]]附近，而驾驶战机坠毁于一处无人居住的森林区。另一架在转场途中的新造苏9战斗机也曾试图拦截U-2。手无寸铁的[[苏9|苏9]]试图撞击U-2，但由于速度差距较大而错过了。鲍尔斯在回忆录《臭鼬工厂》中声称他在弹出座舱时曾在他身后看到有另一名飞行员的降落伞。<!--
Powers' U-2 plane was hit by the first S-75 missile fired. A total of eight were launched; one missile hit a [[MiG-19|MiG-19]] jet fighter sent to intercept the U-2, but could not reach a high enough altitude. The Soviet pilot, Sergey Safronov, crashed his plane in an unpopulated forest area rather than bail out and risk his plane crashing into nearby [[Degtyarsk|Degtyarsk]]. Another Soviet aircraft, a newly manufactured [[Su-9|Su-9]] in transit flight, also attempted to intercept Powers' U-2. The unarmed Su-9 was directed to ram the U-2. The pilot attempted but missed because of the large differences in speed. Powers claimed, as recounted in "The Skunk Works", that upon ejecting he saw the parachute of another pilot deploy behind him.-->

当美国政府得知鲍尔斯在苏联境内失踪时，立刻发表了一份声明，声称一架“气象飞机”在其驾驶员表示“供氧设备发生故障”之后失去踪迹。中情局官员没有意识到的是，飞机以几乎完整的状态下坠毁，并且苏联方面复原了机上的部分设备。鲍尔斯在招供并为其间谍行为公开道歉之前，曾被KGB广泛深入地审问了数月之久<!--When the U.S. government learned of Powers' disappearance over the Soviet Union, they issued a cover statement claiming a "weather plane" had strayed off course after its pilot had "difficulties with his oxygen equipment." What CIA officials did not realize was that the plane crashed almost fully intact, and the Soviets recovered its equipment. Powers was interrogated extensively by the KGB for months before he made a confession and a public apology for his part in espionage.--><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.history.com/this-day-in-history.do?action=tdihVideoCategory&id=52645&HPF_rid=9121459&HPF_mid=1180_T1_Url3 |title=This Day in History — History.com — What Happened Today in History |publisher=History.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-31 |language=en }}{{dead link|date=2017年12月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>。这一事件使得赫鲁晓夫和艾森豪威尔之间的会谈被迫推迟。<!-- The incident set back talks between Khrushchev and Eisenhower. -->1960年8月17日，鲍尔斯被以反苏联的间谍活动为罪名而定罪，被判处有期徒刑十年，其中三年监禁七年[[劳动改造|劳动改造]]。他被关押在莫斯科以东100公里的{{link-en|弗拉基米尔中央监狱|Vladimir Central Prison}}。部分U-2的残骸以及鲍尔斯的制服在靠近莫斯科的莫尼诺空军基地博物馆展出。<!--On August 17, 1960, Powers was convicted of espionage against the Soviet Union and was sentenced to a total of ten years, three years in imprisonment followed by seven years of [[hard_labor|hard labor]]. He was held in [[Vladimir_Central_Prison|Vladimir Central Prison]], 100 miles east of Moscow. The prison contains a small museum with an exhibit on Powers, who allegedly developed a good rapport with Russian prisoners there. Some pieces of the plane and Gary Powers' uniform are on display at the Monino Airbase museum, close to Moscow.-->

1962年2月10日，作为一名众所周知的间谍，鲍尔斯与另一名美国学生{{le|弗雷德瑞克·普萊爾|Frederic Pryor}}一道在德国柏林的[[格利尼克大桥|格利尼克大桥]]被交换回国。被交换的对象是由[[联邦调查局|联邦调查局]]抓捕并以间谍罪判入狱的克格勃[[上校|上校]][[维利亚姆·费舍尔|维利亚姆·费舍尔]]（又名鲁道夫·阿贝尔）。<!--On February 10, 1962, Powers was exchanged, along with American student [[Frederic_Pryor|Frederic Pryor]], in a well-publicized spy swap at the [[Glienicke_Bridge|Glienicke Bridge]] in Berlin, Germany. The exchange was for Soviet [[KGB|KGB]] [[Colonel|Colonel]] [[Vilyam_Genrikhovich_Fisher|Vilyam Fisher]] (aka Rudolf Abel), who had been caught by the FBI and jailed for espionage.

In 2010, CIA documents were released indicating that "top US officials never believed Powers’ account of his fateful flight because it appeared to be directly contradicted by a report from the National Security Agency, the clandestine US network of codebreakers and listening posts. The NSA report remains classified, possibly to spare the blushes of its authors. For it is now possible to piece together what really happened high over Sverdlovsk on May 1, 1960, and to understand why America’s most secretive intelligence agency got it so wrong".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/world/us_and_americas/article7113512.ece |title=CIA documents show US never believed Gary Powers was shot down |publisher=Timesonline.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2012-08-31|language=en}}</ref> -->根据文章援引，根据中情局解密文件表明，鲍尔斯在高空被击落的事实是确凿无疑的。<!--According to the article cited, the still classified NSA report is incorrect based on the CIA documents that were declassified which show that Powers' account of being shot down at altitude was accurate.-->

== 余波 ==
[[File:KellyJohnsonandGaryPowers.jpg|thumb]]与弗朗西斯·加利·鲍尔斯在U-2的前面<!--[[Clarence_Johnson|Kelly Johnson]] and Francis Gary Powers in front of a U-2-->]][[File:U2_Powers_Senate_model.jpg|thumb]]
回國后，鮑爾斯受到冷遇。最初，他被指責應當為他在離開飛機之前未啟動飛機的[[自爆|自毀]]程序，打空檔、引擎熄火、销毁攝影機、[[底片|底片]]以及飞机上相关的[[国家机密|机密]]部件而負責。他也被批評沒有使用中情局提供給他的“{{tsl|en|suicide pill||自殺藥丸}}”來進行自殺。经过中情局、洛克希德公司和空军的大量審問后，1962年3月6日，鲍尔斯出现在由包括参议员{{tsl|en|Richard Russell, Jr.||理查德·拉塞尔}}、参议员{{tsl|en|Prescott Bush||普雷斯科特·布什}}和{{tsl|en|Barry Goldwater, Jr.||老巴里·戈德华特}}主持的参议院武装部队委员会听证会上。最終厘定，鮑爾斯遵守命令，没有透露任何关键資訊给苏联方面，並且“作為一名年輕人，在危險的境地下”進行了自我指導。<!--Powers received a cold reception on his return home. Initially, he was criticized for having failed to activate his aircraft’s [[self-destruct|self-destruct]] charge to destroy the [[camera|camera]], [[photographic_film|photographic film]], and related [[classified_information|classified]] parts of his aircraft before his capture. He was also criticized for not using an optional CIA-issued "[[suicide_pill|suicide pill]]" to kill himself. After being debriefed extensively by the CIA, Lockheed, and the Air Force, on March 6, 1962, Powers appeared before a Senate Armed Services Select Committee hearing chaired by Senator [[Richard_Russell,_Jr.|Richard Russell]] and including Senators [[Prescott_Bush|Prescott Bush]] and [[Barry_Goldwater|Barry Goldwater]] Sr. It was determined that Powers had followed orders, had not divulged any critical information to the Soviets, and had conducted himself “as a fine young man under dangerous circumstances.”--><ref name="CIA0000009451">{{cite web |title = Report of the board of inquiry into the case of francis gary powers |publisher = Central Intelligence Agency |url = http://www.foia.cia.gov/browse_docs.asp?doc_no=0000009451&no_pages=0019&showPage=0001 |format = gif |date = 1962-02-27 |accessdate = 2010-07-12 |page = 1 |language = en |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120323061429/http://www.foia.cia.gov/browse_docs.asp?doc_no=0000009451&no_pages=0019&showPage=0001 |archivedate = 2012-03-23 }}</ref>

1963年至1970年，鲍尔斯在[[洛克希德公司|洛克希德公司]]担任试飞员。在1970年，他与人合作写了一本书，叫做《[[飞越计划_：U-2事件回忆录|飞越计划 ：U-2事件回忆录]]》。之后洛克希德公司解雇了他，此举被人普遍认为是由于书中对中央情报局进行了负面解析。鲍尔斯成为了{{tsl|en|KMZT (AM)||KGIL}}洛杉矶电台的一个空中交通记者。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cnn.com/2012/06/09/us/silver-star-award/index.html?hpt=hp_t1 |title=Cold War pilot Francis Gary Powers to get Silver Star |publisher=CNN.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-31 |language=en |archive-date=2012-07-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120711212959/http://www.cnn.com/2012/06/09/us/silver-star-award/index.html?hpt=hp_t1 |dead-url=no }}</ref><!--Powers worked for [[Lockheed_Corporation|Lockheed]] as a test pilot from 1963 to 1970. In 1970, he co-wrote a book called ''Operation Overflight: A Memoir of the U-2 Incident.'' Lockheed fired him, it was widely believed, because the book cast negative publicity on the CIA. Powers became an airborne traffic reporter for radio station [[KMZT_(AM)|KGIL]] Los Angeles. A fixed-wing pilot, he was then hired by television station [[KNBC|KNBC]] to pilot their "[[telecopter|telecopter]]", a helicopter equipped with externally mounted 360-degree cameras. The telecopter had been in service for years, and was purchased from KTLA, Channel 5.-->

1976年，鮑爾斯的傳記被改編成為電視電影《弗朗西斯·加里·鲍尔斯：U-2事件的真实故事》，李·迈杰斯扮演鮑爾斯。<!--In 1976, Powers' biography (written with [[Curt_Gentry|Curt Gentry]]) became a television movie, ''Francis Gary Powers: The True Story of the U-2 Spy Incident''. [[Lee_Majors|Lee Majors]] played the role of Powers.-->

== 坠机事故 ==
1977年8月1日，鲍尔斯在一次事故中死亡，当时他在[[聖巴巴拉縣_(加利福尼亞州)|圣巴巴拉县]]近郊拍摄灭火场景<ref name="law">{{cite news|url=http://www.hangkonglaw.com/a/feixingyuan/feixingyuanxinwen/2012/1219/33633.html|title=美军飞行员谍海浮沉记|publisher=北青网|date=2012-12-19|accessdate=2013-11-23|language=zh-cn|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150511071451/http://www.hangkonglaw.com/a/feixingyuan/feixingyuanxinwen/2012/1219/33633.html|archivedate=2015-05-11}}</ref>。当他返回时，他的[[貝爾206直升機|贝尔206“喷气别动队员”]]直升机（注册编号N4TV），因燃油耗尽而在距离{{tsl|en|Burbank Airport||伯班克机场}}仅几英里远的{{tsl|en|Sepulveda Dam||塞普尔韦达大坝}}游乐区坠毁<!--Powers died in 1977 in an accident. He had been covering brush fires in [[Santa_Barbara_County|Santa Barbara County]]. As he returned, his [[貝爾206直升機|Bell 206 Jet Ranger]] helicopter, registered N4TV, ran out of fuel and crashed in the [[Sepulveda_Dam|Sepulveda Dam]] Recreation Area several miles short of [[Burbank_Airport|Burbank Airport]].--><ref name="check-six.com">{{cite web |url=http://www.check-six.com/Crash_Sites/Powers-N4TV.htm |title=The Francis Gary Powers Helo Crash |publisher=Check-six.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-31 |language=en |archive-date=2012-06-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120621045453/http://www.check-six.com/Crash_Sites/Powers-N4TV.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[美国国家运输安全委员会|美国国家运输安全委员会]]的报告将坠机的可能原因归因于飞行员失误（糟糕的燃料管理）<!-- The [[National_Transportation_Safety_Board|National Transportation Safety Board]] report attributed the probable cause of the crash to pilot error (poor fuel management).--><ref name="check-six.com"/>。据鲍尔斯之子所述，航空机械师在未告知鲍尔斯的情况下已将先前出现故障的燃油表修好，从而导致鲍尔斯对燃油标量误判<!-- According to Powers' son, an aviation mechanic had repaired a faulty fuel gauge without telling Powers, who misread it.--><ref name="autogenerated1">{{cite web |url=http://phs1.org/U2%20Program/Powers_Helicopter_Crash.htm |title=Powers Helicopter Crash |publisher=Phs1.org |date= |accessdate=2012-08-31 |language=en |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120613182148/http://phs1.org/U2%20Program/Powers_Helicopter_Crash.htm |archivedate=2012-06-13 }}</ref>。在坠机前的最后时刻，鲍尔斯发现迫降区域有儿童在玩耍，因此努力操控直升机飞往别处以避免伤及孩童<!--At the last moment he noticed children playing in the area, and directed the helicopter elsewhere to prevent their deaths.--><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.check-six.com/Crash_Sites/Powers-N4TV.htm |title=Powers' Helo Crash |publisher=Check-six.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-31 |language=en |archive-date=2012-06-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120621045453/http://www.check-six.com/Crash_Sites/Powers-N4TV.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。若非最后时刻的误差，从而破坏他直升机的{{tsl|en|Autorotation (helicopter)||自旋}}下降状态，他可能可以安全降落<!-- If not for the last second deviation, which compromised his [[Autorotation_(helicopter)|autorotative]] descent, he might have landed safely.--><ref name="autogenerated1"/>。

鲍尔斯与她的妻子，两个孩子——迪·鲍尔斯和小弗朗西斯·加里·鲍尔斯以及五个姐妹生活在一起。作为一名空军老兵，鲍尔斯死后被安葬在[[阿灵顿国家公墓|阿灵顿国家公墓]]。<!--Powers was survived by his wife, two children, Dee and Francis Gary Powers Jr., and five sisters. Powers is buried in [[Arlington_National_Cemetery|Arlington National Cemetery]] as an Air Force veteran.--><ref name="check-six.com"/><ref>{{cite web |author=Michael Robert Patterson |url=http://www.arlingtoncemetery.net/francisg.htm |title=Francis Gary Powers, Captain, United States Air Force |publisher=Arlingtoncemetery.net |date= |accessdate=2012-08-31 |language=en |archive-date=2017-12-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171218103643/http://www.arlingtoncemetery.net/francisg.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 所得荣誉 ==
從苏联被送回国之后，中情局于1965年授予其“{{tsl|en|Intelligence Star||情报之星}}”奖章。鲍尔斯原定与其他参与中情局U-2项目的飞行员一道于1963年获得此项表彰，但由于政治原因被迫推迟。<!--Powers received the CIA's [[Intelligence_Star|Intelligence Star]] in 1965 after his return from the Soviet Union. Powers was originally scheduled to receive it in 1963 along with other pilots involved in the CIA's U-2 program, but the award was postponed for political reasons. -->1970年，鲍尔斯出版了他的第一本，也是唯一一本关于空中侦察工作的回忆录《[[赤手空拳和无所畏惧|赤手空拳和无所畏惧]]》<!--In 1970, Powers published his first--and only--book review, on a work about aerial reconnaissance, "Unarmed and Unafraid" by Glenn Infield, in the monthly magazine, Business & Commercial Aviation. "The subject has great interest to me," he said, in submitting his review. (Letter to G. Haber, Managing Editor, BCA)-->

在1998年，最新的解密信息表明，鲍尔斯的任务一直是由美国空军和中情局联合运作。在2000年，U-2事件40周年之际，他的家人代其领受了追授予他的{{tsl|en|Prisoner of War Medal||战俘勋章}}、[[飞行优异十字勋章|飞行优异十字勋章]]和[[国防部服役奖章|国防部服役奖章]]。此外，美国中央情报局局长[[乔治·特尼特|乔治·特尼特]]追授予鲍尔斯以中情局人人期盼的“{{tsl|en|Awards and decorations of the United States government||局长奖章}}”，表彰他在履行职责时极度的忠诚和非凡的勇气。<!--In 2000, on the 40th anniversary of the U-2 Incident, his family was presented his posthumously awarded [[Prisoner_of_War_Medal|Prisoner of War Medal]], [[Distinguished_Flying_Cross_(USA)|Distinguished Flying Cross]], and [[National_Defense_Service_Medal|National Defense Service Medal]]. In addition, CIA Director [[George_Tenet|George Tenet]] authorized Powers to posthumously receive the CIA's coveted [[Awards_and_decorations_of_the_United_States_government#Central_Intelligence_Agency.5B7.5D|Director's Medal]] for extreme fidelity and extraordinary courage in the line of duty.--><ref>{{cite web|url=http://frontpagemag.com/2012/lloyd-billingsley/francis-gary-powers-gets-his-silver-star/2/|title=Francis Gary Powers Gets His Silver Star|publisher=FrontPage Magazine|date=2012-06-20|author=Lloyd Billingsley|accessdate=2012-11-21|language=en|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130203115842/http://frontpagemag.com/2012/lloyd-billingsley/francis-gary-powers-gets-his-silver-star/2/|archivedate=2013-02-03}}</ref>

2012年6月15日，鲍尔斯被追授[[银星勋章|银星勋章]]以表彰其“在莫斯科[[卢比扬卡大楼|卢比扬卡大楼]]（克格勃的代称）忍受近两年严酷的审讯中所展现出的‘特殊的忠诚’。”
<!--On June 15, 2012, Powers was posthumously awarded the [[Silver_Star|Silver Star]] medal for "demonstrating 'exceptional loyalty' while enduring harsh interrogation in the [[Lubyanka_Prison|Lubyanka Prison]] in Moscow for almost two years."--><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.defense.gov/Advisories/Advisory.aspx?AdvisoryID=3450 |title=Press Advisory: Silver Star to be Posthumously Presented to Capt. Francis Gary Powers |publisher=Defense.gov |date= |accessdate=2012-08-31 |language=en |archive-date=2012-10-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121012185541/http://www.defense.gov//advisories/advisory.aspx?advisoryid=3450 |dead-url=no }}</ref>五角大楼的仪式上，空军总参谋长{{tsl|en|Norton Schwartz||诺顿·施瓦茨}}将绶带授予鲍尔斯的孙子，9岁的特里·鲍尔斯和29岁的琳赛·贝里<!-- Air Force Chief of Staff Gen. [[Norton_Schwartz|Norton Schwartz]] presented the decoration to Powers’ grandchildren, Trey Powers, 9, and Lindsey Berry, 29, in a Pentagon ceremony. --><ref>{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/politics/2012/06/u-2-pilot-gary-powers-receives-silver-star/ |title=U-2 Pilot Gary Powers Receives Silver Star - ABC News |publisher=Abcnews.go.com |date=2012-06-15 |accessdate=2012-08-31 |language=en |archive-date=2012-06-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120625205611/http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/politics/2012/06/u-2-pilot-gary-powers-receives-silver-star/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

